Hotword (contextual) biasing for the RNN-T greedy decoder.

Vendored patch against mudler/parakeet.cpp @ e270af73 (PARAKEET_REF in the
Dockerfile). Applied by the Dockerfile builder stage with `git apply` right
after checkout. Adds `parakeet_capi_set_hotwords(ctx, ids, lens, n, boost)`
(token-id sequences; the Python bridge tokenizes) and bumps the C ABI 4 -> 5.

Upstream-PR-shaped on purpose: when (a version of) this lands upstream,
delete this file, drop the `git apply` line, bump PARAKEET_REF, and re-point
engine.py at the upstream API if it differs.

