+// Set hotword (contextual) biasing for subsequent transcribe_* calls on `ctx`.
+// Each of `n_phrases` phrases is a token-id sequence (tokenize the phrase text
+// with the model's tokenizer first): `ids` is the concatenation of all phrases'
+// token ids and `lens[i]` is the number of tokens in phrase i. During RNN-T
+// greedy decode, `boost` is added to the logit of any token that starts or
+// continues a phrase, nudging the argmax toward known vocabulary. boost == 0 or
+// n_phrases == 0 clears biasing. No-op on a NULL ctx. (Added in ABI v5.)
+void parakeet_capi_set_hotwords(parakeet_ctx* ctx, const int* ids,
+                                const int* lens, int n_phrases, float boost);
